[[File:PE-mapa-Paranatama.png|thumb|right|250px|Paranatama in [[Pernambuco]].]] '''Paranatama''' is a municipality/city in the state of [[Pernambuco]] in [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009 was 12.441 and the total area is 230.88&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste]] of Pernambuco * Boundaries - [[Caetés, Pernambuco|Caetés]] ('''N'''); [[Saloá]] ('''S'''); [[Garanhuns]] ('''E'''); [[Pedra, Pernambuco|Pedra]] ('''W'''). * Area - 230.88&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 879 m * Hidrography - [[Mundaú River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hipoxerófila]] * Clima - Transition between [[tropical]] hot and humid and, [[semi arid]] hot * Annual average temperature - 20.8 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 192&nbsp;km
==Economy==
The main economic activity in '''Paranatama''' is [[agribusiness]], especially [[cattle]], [[goat]], [[pig]], [[sheep]], and [[chicken]] farming; and plantations of [[bean]]s, [[manioc]], [[coffee]] and [[maize|corn]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}
